== Training Withdraw ==

'''Training Withdraw''' (also called '''Withdraw Training''' or simply '''Withdraw''') is one of the most important mechanics in Vulcore. It refers to the process of deliberately withdrawing from battles to reduce the '''KCharge (KC)''' cost of future withdrawals.

=== What is Withdraw? ===
When a Controller withdraws from a battle, it costs '''KCharge'''. The cost of withdrawing decreases as the Controller trains it — specifically, by withdrawing from battles repeatedly, the KC cost per withdraw drops. A fully trained Withdraw costs only '''1 KC''' to execute.

=== Why is it Important? ===
* Allows safe escape from dangerous encounters (Angels, Matriarchs with Deflector Coil, overwhelming squads)
* Enables farming in Scaven territory without risking bot loss
* Critical for surviving encounters that would otherwise destroy the squad
* Allows strategic retreat from Bulwark squads, EX-series, and other dangerous enemies

=== How to Train Withdraw ===
# Enter [[Scaven]] territory via the Matriarch Mission
# Find [[Scaven]] Watchtowers or Forts
# Initiate battle, then immediately '''Withdraw All''' bots
# Repeat 4–6 times until Withdraw costs only 1 KC

'''Key notes:'''
* Withdraw from Watchtowers or easy battles — not from dangerous squads
* When fighting normal squads for Withdraw training: kill dangerous units (Knights, Champions), then withdraw all except one bot (e.g., [[Overseer|Zodiac]]), then withdraw the last bot too

=== Withdraw in Combat ===
During combat, the '''Withdraw''' option removes a bot from the battle. Strategic use:
* Withdraw damaged bots to preserve them
* Withdraw all bots when a battle is going badly
* When fighting Matriarchs: if you cannot drain the Deflector Coil shield in the first turn, '''withdraw immediately'''
* When encountering Angels: '''withdraw in one turn''' — do not let them fire

== Patrol Phases ==

Vulcore progression is divided into '''Patrols''' — each patrol ends when the Controller returns to the Workshop to upgrade. The following is a comprehensive guide to each patrol phase.

=== Patrol 1 — The Foundation ===

==== Workshop Setup ====
* Start with a '''[[Valadin]]''' chassis (see [[Vulcore Plain]] for zone overview)
* Outfit: Ion V2 Reactor, 1× Argon Laser
* Go to CCU Training Center; fight lone Fleas until AI Level 1
* Exit Training; spend 5 upgrade points on Weapon Tech
* Replace Argon Laser with 2× Baron Laser; buy 2× Baron Shield
* Add Phase Modulator and Motion Tracker

