== Important Mechanics ==

=== KCharge (KC) ===
KCharge is the patrol timer/resource. Every action in the outlands costs KC. When KC reaches 0, the patrol ends and the Controller is returned to the Workshop. Key KC costs:
* Moving/patrolling: 1 KC per step
* Withdrawing from battle: variable (reduced by [[Training Withdraw|Withdraw training]])
* Entering sub-zones: variable

'''Conserve KC by:'''
* Skipping avoidable fights when not farming
* Training Withdraw to reduce its KC cost to 1
* Not entering Canyons or Caves unnecessarily

=== Battle Merit (BM) ===
Battle Merit is a measure of the squad's total combat power. Higher BM means:
* Enemies scale harder (more dangerous encounters)
* Better rewards from Azra and other encounters
* More dangerous Sulphur encounters (keep BM under 1.5M for early Sulphur runs)

=== Greed ===
Greed is a buff obtained from the [[Fallen]] (requires −25 alignment). It multiplies all cash bounties by '''10×''' for a limited duration (approximately 500 KC or until a console is taken).

'''Rules while under Greed:'''
* '''Never take a console''' — cash bonuses from consoles will end Greed
* Focus on Tag Droids and Azra for maximum cash
* Avoid Renegade Bases (consoles inside)
* Avoid Plateaus (consoles inside) unless specifically farming Bulwark segments

=== Dark Union (Fallen Union) ===
Dark Union adds powerful [[Fallen]] bots to the squad but drains XP and cash while active. The drain grows the longer you patrol.

'''Fallen bots in Dark Union:'''
* 2× Demon
* 2× Fiend
* 1× Baal or 1× Beelzebub

'''When to use Dark Union:'''
* Patrol 4: Required to access Master Controllers
* Patrol 5–6: Optional; useful for Sulphur runs with extra firepower

=== Crowns ===
Crowns are a currency obtained from Scaven Burial Mounds and the Sun Ritual. They are used to hire Scaven mercs and purchase items at the Outpost.

* Sun Ritual: 4 Crowns per completion
* Burial Mounds: variable
* Delivering Crowns at the Outpost converts them to Mercreds (approximately 275 Mercreds per 28 Crowns)

=== EXP Multipliers ===
EXP multipliers increase the experience gained from battles. They are obtained from:
* Scaven Settlements (EXP chips)
* Random encounters
* Purchased with Mercreds

'''Important:''' Only attack normal Scaven squads when you have 3× EXP or more (to make the KC cost worthwhile).

=== Deflector Coil ===
A special shield ring carried by some Scaven Matriarchs. Bots with Deflector Coil cannot be drained without a critical hit. '''Always withdraw immediately''' if you cannot drain a Matriarch with Deflector Coil in the first turn.

=== Shield Projection ===
Many enemies in Vulcore use projected shields. Key points:
* Projected shields must be depleted before armour damage can be dealt effectively
* Draining the projector bot's reactor removes the projected shield from all squadmates
* Prioritise draining shield projectors in combat

== Cash & Mercred Farming ==

=== Early Cash Farming (Patrol 1) ===
* '''Tag Droids''' — primary source; farm with Greed active for 10× bounty
* '''Azra's Arena''' — significant cash reward; do after getting Greed
* '''Stun Lasers''' — sell for 900 cash each
* '''Plateaus''' — enter after Azra for additional Tag Droids

=== Mid-Game Cash Farming (Patrols 2–3) ===
* '''Tag Droids + Greed''' — still the primary method
* '''Azra''' — major cash injection each patrol
* '''Lava Fields''' — Phoenix squads and Magma Lords alongside cash farming
* '''Plateaus''' — Mining Bases and Renegade Bases for Bulwark segments + cash

=== Late-Game Cash Farming (Patrols 4–6) ===
* '''Sulphur Pits''' — high-value enemies; Renegade Workshops and Crusader segments
* '''Azra''' — still valuable; buy Azra coords before leaving patrol if you have 800 Mercreds
* '''Federate Transmissions''' — each gives approximately 1 shield worth of cash (33k each)
* '''Argon Lasers''' — buy and sell for cash management

=== Mercred Farming ===
* '''Tag Droid Missions''' — 3 Mercreds per mission; do 4× for 12 Mercreds early
* '''Cave Crystal Missions''' — reliable Mercred source throughout Vulcore
* '''Crowns''' — deliver to Outpost for Mercreds (28 Crowns ≈ 275 Mercreds)
* '''Scaven Settlements''' — get Mercreds from settlement rewards

=== Credits (Crowns) Farming ===
* '''Sun Ritual''' — 4 Crowns per completion; most reliable Crown source
* '''Burial Mounds''' — variable Crowns
* '''Scaven Settlements''' — occasional Crown rewards

== Things to Watch Out For ==

=== Angels ===
* '''Always withdraw from Angels in one turn''' — they are extremely dangerous
* Killing Angels grants −4 alignment (useful for alignment farming in Patrol 3+)
* Never fight Angels in Patrol 1 or 2

=== Matriarchs with Deflector Coil ===
* Cannot be drained without a critical hit
* '''Withdraw immediately''' if you cannot drain them in the first turn
* Check the shield ring before engaging

=== Magma Fortresses ===
* Extremely dangerous — do not attack
* Found in Lava Fields

=== Annihilators ===
* Avoid in early Sulphur runs
* Only fight with 100+ speed Reapers and strong shielding
* Especially dangerous when accompanied by Shamans

=== EX-Series Renegades (EX21–EX24) ===
* Have Shield Neutralisers — must be drained before they fire
* Found in Sulphur Pits
* Drain them in the first turn or withdraw

=== Horrors ===
* Thermal Dawn weapon — devastating
* Fire rate depends on Shaman support:
  * No Shaman: fire on turn 3
  * 1 Shaman: fire on turn 2
  * 2 Shamans: fire on turn 1
* Drain the Horror (or the Shaman) before they can fire

=== Renegade Base Lords ===
* Normal Base Lord is harmless
* Any other Base Lord variant must be drained
* Check before engaging

=== Consoles ===
* '''Never take a console while under Greed''' — cash bonuses end Greed
* Consoles in Plateaus and Renegade Bases can contain Bulwark segments

=== Fallen Coords Cost ===
* Each Fallen coord taken costs 10 alignment
* Do not take too many coords — you need −100 alignment spare after Patrol 3

=== Tag Trackers ===
* If an enemy squad has a Reaper, retreat from Tag Trackers
* Tag Trackers can be dangerous in early Patrol 1

